[8] China (Yunnan)
Date: Wed 6 Mar 2013
Source: China Daily, Yunnan.cn [edited]
Wed, 6 Mar 2013 17:18:21 +0100
http://usa.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2013-03/05/content_16280775.htm


As of the end of February 2013, 151 cases of measles had been confirmed in Kunming, capital of Yunnan province, with 2 deaths caused by this highly contagious disease, Yunnan.cn, an official news portal in the province, reported on Tuesday [5 Mar 2013]. To contain the spread of the disease, Kunming on Wednesday [6 Mar 2013] will begin offering free vaccinations for all children in the city, the report said, citing the Kunming Center for Disease Control.

