[9] USA (NJ)
Date: Fri 8 Mar 2013
Source: News 12, the Bronx [edited]
http://bronx.news12.com/news/doh-issues-public-health-alert-in-possible-measles-case-at-somerset-medical-center-1.4781255?qr=1


A person suspected of having measles may have exposed people at Somerset Medical Center. The New Jersey Department of Health has issued a public health alert related to a possible measles case.

The state Department of Health has identified a person suspected of having measles who may have exposed people at Somerset Medical Center between 4-6 Mar 2013. The Department of Health advises anyone who visited the medical center between the following dates to immediately contact a health provider:

4 Mar 2013 - between 8 a.m. and 6 p.m.
5 Mar 2013 - between 8 a.m. and 6 p.m.
6 Mar 2013 - between 8 a.m. and 2 p.m.

Measles symptoms include rash, high fever, cough, runny nose, and red, watery eyes.

